shared_text:
Litchfield Community Schools
February 11, 2017 at 3:46 PM ·

On Monday, February 13th school will be released early at 11:00 am.This is both an unscheduled early release and 30 minutes earlier than normal.

The reason for this release is due to one of our staff member’s experienced an unexpected tragedy and lost their spouse.

In order for staff and community members alike to represent support we have elected to enact this early release as an option for staff members to attend the services scheduled for Monday afternoon.

If you have any questions, do not hesitate to call the front office Monday morning and we will assist you however we may.

Thank you so much for your understanding in supporting one of our own staff members through this difficult time.

shared_text:
Litchfield Community Schools updated their status.
January 27, 2017 at 6:19 PM ·

Parents, guardians, and community of LCS:

Based upon today's late release, the staff and administration at Litchfield Community Schools would like to thank you for your support and patience in assuring the safety of our kids. We received a disturbing communication from a parent that seemed to be isolated to one particular family and staff member. However, to be sure we put safety first until the matter was resolved we enacted a soft lockdown. As local authorities and building staff assessed absolute safety in the situation we then released accordingly. We will always place safety as a priority and thank you for your understanding as we put safety first with our team of staff in the students' best interests.
